FILE: core/rings.py
AUTHOR: Shiva (Claude Code) + Sean Campbell

SUMMARY
-------
Initial implementation of RINGS — the trunk routing and interpretation layer.

RINGS is the central router. It interprets intent, routes to the right agent,
injects knowledge context, and manages the Node Ring Registry + Pigeon contract.

THE ROOT CAUSE FIX
------------------
Willow 1.x context_injector.py line 49 hardcodes:
  query="system state current tasks"
for all Kart knowledge retrievals regardless of what the conversation is about.
This is why Gemini kept returning [MISSING_DATA] on Sean's own knowledge.

RINGS 1.4 replaces that pattern with:
  interpret(message) → semantic query extracted from the actual user message
  build_context(username, agent_name, loam_db_path, message=None, query=None)

Any agent that calls build_context() with message= gets query-aware retrieval.
No more hardcoded strings.

DESIGN DECISIONS
----------------
1. interpret(message) → str: lightweight semantic query extraction.
   No fleet call — regex + keyword extraction. Fast enough for every turn.
2. route(task, agents) → str: simple keyword-based agent recommendation.
   Deterministic. No LLM for routing (avoids latency + recursion risk).
3. Ring registry state stored in artifacts/{username}/rings.json.
   No boot.py dependency. Portable.
4. Pigeon contract: dataclasses, validate_inbound() strict.
5. build_context() falls back gracefully if LOAM unavailable.
6. Execution loop (KartOrchestrator) lives in GRAFT, not here.
   RINGS = interpret + route + inject. GRAFT = execute + govern.

PUBLIC API
----------
# Intent
interpret(message) → str
route(task, agents) → str

# Context Injection
build_context(username, agent_name, loam_db_path,
              vine_db_path=None, message=None, query=None,
              max_chars=800) → str

# Ring Registry
load_rings(state_path) → NodeRings
save_rings(state_path, rings) → None
enroll_peer(state_path, peer_id) → NodeRings
enroll_gate(state_path, gate_path) → tuple[bool, str]
ring_status(state_path) → dict

# Pigeon Contract
make_pigeon(content, gate_conditions, sender, seed_packet=None) → dict
validate_inbound(payload) → tuple[bool, str]

GOVERNANCE: soil-initial-2026-03-03.applied, loam-initial-2026-03-03.applied
